                            <comment id="17895783" author="benedict" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 20:03:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a string being shared by gossip that&apos;s &amp;gt; 65K characters long. More than that is hard to decipher from the stack trace.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895785" author="benedict" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 20:04:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess probably schema?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895786" author="rustyrazorblade" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 20:09:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, there&apos;s 800 tables, each of which with a secondary index.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895788" author="benedict" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 20:16:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess perhaps 5.0 introduced some schema feature that makes the schema definition longer?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m surprised this hasn&apos;t been a problem for anyone before, 65K isn&apos;t that large for schema definitions. Fortunately TCM resolves this in 5.1+. Fixing this in 5.0 and before requires a messaging version bump.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895811" author="dcapwell" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 22:01:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looking at trunk (so slightly different logic); org.apache.cassandra.index.IndexStatusManager#propagateLocalIndexStatus&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (Gossiper.instance.isEnabled())
            {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; newStatus = JsonUtils.JSON_OBJECT_MAPPER.writeValueAsString(states);
                statusPropagationExecutor.submit(() -&amp;gt; {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// schedule gossiper update asynchronously to avoid potential deadlock when another thread is holding
&lt;/span&gt;                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// gossiper taskLock.
&lt;/span&gt;                    VersionedValue value = StorageService.instance.valueFactory.indexStatus(newStatus);
                    Gossiper.instance.addLocalApplicationState(ApplicationState.INDEX_STATUS, value);
                });
            }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this is the only thing I see that isn&apos;t basically fixed (other than token)... I wasn&apos;t expecting to see JSON....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895813" author="dcapwell" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 22:02:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=maedhroz&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;maedhroz&quot;&gt;maedhroz&lt;/a&gt; looks like this was added to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18058&quot; title=&quot;In-memory index and query path&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18058&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18058&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895826" author="maedhroz" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2024 23:01:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, this is the map of index name -&amp;gt; status that informs &lt;tt&gt;IndexStatusManager&lt;/tt&gt; and allows us to avoid indexes that aren&apos;t in a queryable state on particular replicas. We can probably reduce the size of the JSON by simply using a numeric representation of the &lt;tt&gt;Index.Status&lt;/tt&gt; and by factoring keyspace names out of the fully qualified index names. We could continue to write the old format until the cluster stabilizes at the 5.0.x version that can &lt;em&gt;read&lt;/em&gt; the new format.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s kind of a band-aid to raise the ceiling. Open to other approaches...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17895832" author="dcapwell" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2024 00:23:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;for 5.0 stability that makes sense.  Would need to look closer at the details to see how we can improve more in 5.1, but this makes sense as a bug fix in 5.0.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17896031" author="rustyrazorblade" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2024 16:51:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Instead of using JSON for the Map&amp;lt;String, Index.Status&amp;gt; states how about 2-5 bytes per index:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[index: vint, 1-4 bytes][status: short, 1 byte]&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not exactly human readable but we can pack a ton of data in, and can even compress it with zSTD at the end.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17896042" author="maedhroz" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2024 17:08:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could also use the index UUID I guess instead of the full name...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17896045" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2024 17:18:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Full name may compress better if that is used though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17896051" author="maedhroz" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2024 17:50:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For shorter keyspace and table names, it might not be helpful at all. I&apos;ll see what just factoring out the keyspace name looks like...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17897981" author="maedhroz" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2024 16:46:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Started &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3678&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;working&lt;/a&gt; on this. Just moving to an integer enum representation cuts out ~13k w/ 800 indexes, assuming they&apos;re all &lt;tt&gt;BUILD_SUCCEEDED&lt;/tt&gt;. The rest is going to depend somewhat on keyspace name length...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The mixed cluster situation will be interesting. I think we actually want to write the new format when the cluster min version is &amp;lt; 5.0.0, given we&apos;re upgrading from a version that ignores this anyway. Then we only want to deal with writing something backwards compatible for min versions between 5.0.0 and 5.0.2 (or 5.0.3 if that gets cut before I finish this). The 4.0.5 -&amp;gt; 5.0.x upgrade mentioned in the description above has a much better chance of success, since it will never attempt to write the more bloated format.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17898481" author="maedhroz" created="Fri, 15 Nov 2024 05:17:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3678&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;a patch&lt;/a&gt; that does &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3678/files#diff-ee36b7c0b49bfda5e64261af0edfeb207ffe66b00e71f9059f503d5567e1bf84R274&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;roughly what I&apos;ve mentioned&lt;/a&gt; in my previous comments, along with some mixed mode enhancements to a couple existing tests around the index status manager. CI is looking pretty clean:  &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13072850/13072850_ci_summary.html&quot; title=&quot;ci_summary.html attached to CASSANDRA-20058&quot;&gt;ci_summary.html&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ready for review for whoever is interested...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17899270" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 18 Nov 2024 21:21:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 in GH with comments.  In the single index case there &quot;should&quot; be at least 3 char savings (more depending on the status), but as you have more indexes in the same keyspace the savings adds up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch doesn&apos;t solve the problem, but does increase the limit before the problem pops up again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17900175" author="maedhroz" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2024 20:41:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;trunk &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13072999/13072999_ci_summary-1.html&quot; title=&quot;ci_summary-1.html attached to CASSANDRA-20058&quot;&gt;CI results &lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  are clean w/ the exception of some env-related problems in the Python upgrade dtests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
